Author-Name:  Kahn, Barbara E
Author-Name:  Moore, William L
Title: 
 The Influence of External Constraints on Brand Choice: The Lone-Alternative Effect.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 119-27
Issue: 1
Volume: 18
Year: 1991
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 In an earlier "Journal of Consumer Research" article, Kahn, Moore, and
 Glazer examined the phenomenon of constrained choice in experimental
 settings and found empirical results that ran counter to generally
 accepted models of hierarchical choice (e.g., preference trees). In this
 article, the authors reexamine those findings. Specifically, their main
 purposes are (1) to provide an explanation for the deviations from
 accepted theoretical models, (2) to suggest operational measures for the
 new constructs identified by Kahn, Moore, and Glazer, and (3) to propose a
 modification of hierarchical models that improves choice prediction by
 adjusting for bias against lone alternatives.


